
Overview of adj glib

The adj glib has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                          
1. glib -- (marked by lack of intellectual depth; "glib generalizations"; "a glib response to a complex question")
2. glib, pat, slick -- (having only superficial plausibility; "glib promises"; "a slick commercial")
3. glib, glib-tongued, smooth-tongued -- (artfully persuasive in speech; "a glib tongue"; "a smooth-tongued hypocrite")
